annotationA: Malate dehydrogenase 2 is one of the enzymes in the tricarboxylic acid cycle in mitochondria; Belongs to the LDH/MDH superfamily
annotationB: Glucose-6-phosphate isomerase activity; phosphogluconate dehydrogenase (decarboxylating) activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: glycolytic process; gluconeogenesis
